</p>
<p>The etiquette of expressing sympathy involves considering the relationship with the bereaved, the cultural context, and the nature of the loss. A heartfelt, handwritten note often carries more weight than a quick text message, though a brief message of support can be appropriate in certain situations.  Regardless of the format, sincerity and genuine concern are paramount. Avoid overly formal language, instead opting for a warm and personal tone reflecting your true feelings.  Focus on offering comfort and support rather than trying to provide solutions or minimize their pain.</p>
    

